summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsNARS Light Reflecting Foundation is an advanced makeup-skincare hybrid that instantly blurs and smooths, while visibly improving skin's clarity over time.*
details: DetailsBenefitsBreathable, medium buildable foundation instantly conceals redness and dark spots, and blurs wrinkles, pores, and texture.Powered by 70% skincare ingredients to visibly improve clarity and Light Reflecting Complex to enhance luminosity.For most skin types, including sensitive. All-day wear.Allure 2022 Best of Beauty Award WinnerResearch ResultsIMMEDIATE: Reveals a more even skin tone by +93%** (**Based on a clinical study, immediate results on 31 women.)LONG TERM: Improves the appearance of skin clarity over time, even after makeup is removed* (*Based on a six-week clinical study of 31 women.)Key IngredientsBIOMIMETIC OAT: Visibly improves clarity by reducing the appearance of redness, while helping to soothe and calm the look of skin.JAPANESE LILYTURF: Immediately strengthens skin's barrier, helping to maintain its moisture.CACAO PEPTIDES & MILK THISTLE: Help reduce the negative effect of blue light and other environmental stressors.Item 2591117How To UseDispense a pearl-sized amount of Light Reflecting Foundation and warm with fingertips.Apply foundation starting at the center of the face and blend out with fingertips.Focus on one area at a time and blend well.Finish with Light Reflecting Setting Powder to set makeup and add dimension.This product comes in a recyclable glass bottle. When finished, remove the pump and recycle the glass bottle.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, C9-12 Alkane, Butylene Glycol, Undecane, Tridecane, Isodecyl Neopentanoate, Hydrogenated Polyisobutene, Polyglyceryl-6 Polyricinoleate, Polyglyceryl-2 Diisostearate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Diisostearyl Malate, Glycerin, Synthetic Wax, Sodium Chloride, Ophiopogon Japonicus Root Extract, Ascophyllum Nodosum Extract, Theobroma Cacao (Cocoa) Seed Extract, Curcuma Longa (Turmeric) Root Extract, Silybum Marianum Fruit Extract, Aluminum Hydroxide, Magnesium Chloride, Sodium Dilauramidoglutamide Lysine, Tocopherol, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Ethylhexylglycerin, Pentylene Glycol, Hydroxyphenyl Propamidobenzoic Acid, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Citric Acid, Sea Water/Maris Aqua/Eau De Mer, Trisodium Edta, Barium Sulfate, Alumina, Chlorphenesin, Phenoxyethanol, Potassium Sorbate, [+/-(May Contain/Peut Contenir): Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Mica, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891)].Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

reviews.headline: My Fave
reviews.comments: I don't love the price, but I do love how it looks on my textured skin. It's also the closest match I have ever had. It appears skin like, is smoothing, and mixes well with all of my skin care. I wear the shade Lagos, and I can only find it at Ulta, I hope they don't get rid of it!!!

reviews.headline: I wanted to love this so much...
reviews.comments: I wanted so much to love this foundation and make it work, but it just didn't for me which is sad because it did help my skin.  It oxidized on me, settled into every line, wrinkle, and pore, and looked like a shiny mask. The amount of money I've spent on this foundation and trying various things to make it work is obnoxious so I have to replace it.

reviews.headline: Moisturizing and not drying
reviews.comments: Switched to NARS after using Estee and I love how dewy (but not too dewy) and natural this looks on my skin. Feels natural without feeling heavy.

reviews.headline: Looks amazing but can't get past the smell
reviews.comments: This foundation is absolutely gorgeous. It goes on beautifully and stays throughout the day. It is definitely a dewy finish it that is what you are looking for. Unfortunately i could not get past the smell. I am not super sensitive when it comes to smells, but this straight up smells like im putting bug spray or something on my face. Its not just a light smell either its very strong and pungent.

reviews.headline: caused breakouts
reviews.comments: I do get hormonal breakouts at times (I'm 53), but not THAT bad, I really think this made my skin break out. And the match quiz did not help me, Valarius is too orange for me. Pretty disappointing and a waste of quite a few dollars.

reviews.headline: Um no
reviews.comments: I've spent over 25 years wearing EsteeLauder, converted to Revlon to break up costs and to get a tad more moisture as I age.  EL I'm Cashew color.  I was matched up Barcelona (which was too light for me) or Valencia (which was too orange for me). Revlon I have to buy 2 colors to mix.  Nars, well I love their blushes.  Their foundation seemed to be loved by many,  so I thought I'd try out of boredom.... first off, when I say it's runny,  I mean,  you literally need a drop. its almost like I dumped an entire bottle of serum into my foundation.  Yes,  that's how runny it is,  even when rubbing into my face.  I looked like a wet wax face.  It felt uncomfortable like I wanted to itch it off. Even with a setting powder it was wet.  Other makeup did NOT blend well at all either. Side note,  I have PCOS, so I need full coverage.  This is probably the furthest from medium/full/build able coverage.  So it's a huge no for me.  Not only that,  during the day I kept getting a wiff of something rancid on my face.  I have sensitive skin. Made where I shave,  turn red and seap through.  I'll stick with what I use.  Love Nars, but not the foundation.  Probably perfect for people who want a BB cream lol

reviews.headline: Turns Orange!
reviews.comments:
I wore this foundation for a full day to do a wear test and see how the product looked from running around all day... I'll give it a 7/10.

Shade match (Oslo) was perfect!... for a hour. Got in the car, flicked open the mirror, and BAM! Orange! Nothing else wrong with the product though. 

I'll compliment the formula. I have combination skin and a lot of products get patchy around my nose and the apples of my cheeks. This foundation didnt, however, I did have to apply multiple layers for full coverage. Definitely buildable!

If the product didnt oxidize so much it would've been 10/10, 5 stars, but I did end up returning the foundation.

reviews.headline: Returned it
reviews.comments: I did not like this.  Texture was like an extra thin serum and I found it hard to work with.   Also settled into wrinkles.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: Ive been using this foundation for years not and nothing compares.

reviews.headline: Love this!
reviews.comments: Great color match for my skin, love the thinner texture, gives medium to full coverage and doesn't look heavy or cakey on my skin

reviews.headline: Marquises-Wish I tried it sooner!
reviews.comments: Foundation is beautiful on my skin, one of the best colour matches ever, like it was made exactly for my skin. Very natural appearance, covers slight imperfections even with a light application. Very comfortable on skin even in the ungodly heat of summer.

reviews.headline: YES YULONG!üëèüëè

FINALLY a perfect color match for my pale skin!
Hydrating, but not in a heavy way!

reviews.headline: LOVE
reviews.comments: It's been such a journey finding a formula and shade that works for me. I'm absolutely in love with this foundation and its build-ability and find myself doing my make up more often because of it

reviews.headline: great foundation and the color was perfect
reviews.comments: a great foundation

reviews.headline: Loveeeeee it
reviews.comments: This is my favorite foundation! Definitely worth your money. I have dry skin and this foundation hydrates while not leaving too much of a dewy finish. Would recommend!!

reviews.headline: Beautiful but not for the girlies who have acne scars
reviews.comments: Its truly a beautiful foundation, very light weight however it does not cover my acne scars üò© ive tried to built it up as well. Unfortunately will be returning for aomething more full coverage!

reviews.headline: Great buildable coverage for mature skin
reviews.comments: This brand was recommended to me by a sales clerk and I love it. Some foundations are heavy and actually accentuate fine lines, but this one is lightweight and doesn't sit or cake in any creases or lines. Great for mature skin.

reviews.headline: Doesn't last
reviews.comments: I really wanted to like this foundation but it melts super easily even with lots of setting spray. I have normal-oily skin and it is summer now but it just does not stay on well. It initially does blend nice and is lightweight though.

reviews.headline: Great for mature skin
reviews.comments: This is the only foundation that I have found that does not separate.  I have spent a small fortune trying to find a foundation  that works for me only to be disappointed so many times. I like the fact that this is not drying. It has a slight dewy finish, but not too much. I have almost used an entire bottle. I will purchase again.

reviews.headline: Yulong is perfect!!
reviews.comments: When I tell you shade Yulong is the perfect shade for the pale girls who are more neutral but a little pink omg. Ive never had a better foundation match ever and the finish is so skinlike plus it has skincare benefits like okay girl! Only thing i dislike is how tight fitting the cap is, makes me worried im going to accidentally throw it or something trying to get it off lol

Wore it for 11 hours and it didn't move and was not oily. I'm in the shade Deep 5 Zambie. It definitely makes your skin glow in a healthy way.
faceoff_positive.headline: My first Nars

faceoff_negative.comments: I had the opportunity to ty the NARS light reflecting foundation. The color didn't match me the way other foundation do, but it did provide great coverage without more than a dime-quarter size amount. The foundation didn't cake at all and didn't run after a spin work out. Overall, I think it's a great foundation for those who like NARS foundations. It just didn't work for me color matching wise.
